This is a custom n8n node for Twelve Data API.

PROJECT CONTEXT:

- Building an n8n community node (a plugin for n8n automation tool)

- Target: Financial data API (stocks, forex, crypto)

- Using TypeScript programming language

- Auto-generating from OpenAPI specification



CODING STANDARDS:

- Use TypeScript strict mode (catch more errors)

- Follow n8n node development guidelines

- Use @devlikeapro/n8n-openapi-node for automatic generation

- API documentation source: https://api.twelvedata.com/doc/swagger/openapi.json

- Base code patterns on the GitHub Issues example in this repo



WHEN I ASK FOR HELP:

- Explain what the code does in simple terms

- Point out where files should go

- Help debug errors clearly

- Suggest best practices for n8n nodes



REMEMBER:

- This is my first custom n8n node

- Explain technical terms when you use them

- Show me where to put files in the folder structure



ENDPOINT TESTING & DOCUMENTATION:

When I test an API endpoint and share the results, you MUST follow this rigorous process:

## MANDATORY DOCUMENTATION TEMPLATE

Every endpoint test MUST be documented in docs/OPENAPI_ANALYSIS.md under "## Endpoint Testing Results" using this exact structure:

```markdown
### [Endpoint Name] - `[HTTP_METHOD] [/endpoint/path]`

**Test Date:** [ISO 8601 timestamp]  
**Tested By:** Femi  
**Response Time:** [milliseconds]ms

#### Canonical Test Command
```bash
curl -X [METHOD] "https://api.twelvedata.com[/path]?param1=value1&param2=value2" \
  -H "Authorization: apikey YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -H "Accept: application/json"
```

#### Request Details
- **HTTP Method:** [GET/POST/etc]
- **Base URL:** https://api.twelvedata.com
- **Endpoint Path:** [/path]
- **Headers:**
  - Authorization: apikey [API_KEY]
  - Accept: application/json

#### Parameters

**Required Parameters:**
| Parameter | Type | Description | Example Value |
|-----------|------|-------------|---------------|
| param1 | string | Description | "value1" |

**Optional Parameters:**
| Parameter | Type | Description | Default | Example Value |
|-----------|------|-------------|---------|---------------|
| param2 | string | Description | N/A | "value2" |

